  <T n="name">0xD9AD90E3<!--String: "Screenshots & Videos"--></T>
  <L n="slides">
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_ScreenshotsAndVideos_1.png">2f7d0004:00000000:741b5aae22d2b510</T>
      <T n="text">0x49C62833<!--String: "Capture your best (or worst) Sims moments with <b><font color='#199C2C'>screenshots</font></b> and <b><font color='#199C2C'>videos</font></b>! In Live Mode, in the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Camera Options</font></b>, you can access buttons to take a screenshot, start and stop recording a video, and open the Screenshot Capture Manager.\n\nYou can also take screenshots with the <b><font color='#199C2C'>[C]</font></b> key and record videos with the <b><font color='#199C2C'>[V]</font></b> key on your keyboard. These shortcuts allow you to take screenshots in Create a Sim, and take screenshots and videos in Build Mode.\n\nCheck out the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Camera Control Lessons</font></b> to learn more about how to control the Game Camera so you can line up the perfect shot!"--></T>
    </U>
    <U>
      <T n="image" p="InGame\UI\tutorial\Client\Beginner\Beginner_ScreenshotsAndVideos_2.png">2f7d0004:00000000:741b5aae22d2b513</T>
      <T n="text">0x6805E2C1<!--String: "In the <b><font color='#199C2C'>Screenshot Capture Manager</font></b>, you can delete and add descriptions to screenshots.\n\nYou can also access your screenshots and videos in a <b><font color='#199C2C'>folder</font></b> on your computer. It’s located at Documents > Electronic Arts > The Sims 4  > Screenshots, or Recorded Videos."--></T>
    </U>
  </L>
